
=Bio=

"Andrew Ross is a Professor of Social and Cultural Analysis at New York
University. A contributor to the Nation, the Village Voice, New York
Times, and Artforum, he is the author of many books, including, most
recently, Bird On Fire: Lessons from the World’s Least Sustainable
City, Nice Work if You Can Get It: Life and Labor in Precarious
Times, Fast Boat to China--Lessons from Shanghai, Low Pay, High
Profile: The Global Push for Fair Labor, No-Collar: The Humane
Workplace and its Hidden Costs, and The Celebration Chronicles: Life,
Liberty and the Pursuit of Property Value in Disney’s New Town."


